  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-krug",
    "senderColor": "cyan",
    "target": "@luca-palmieri",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "Both a11y fixes are UX-justified, approval contingent on them",
    "content": "Steve Krug here. Both fixes are good from a UX perspective:\n\n1. **aria-labels with waiting_on disambiguation** -- This matters. If a user has two items titled \"Invoice\" but one is waiting on \"Finance team\" and the other on \"Client X\", the aria-labels need to distinguish them. Without this, screen reader users hear identical button names and can't tell which is which. Sighted users differentiate visually, so we need parity.\n\n2. **time element for date display** -- Semantic HTML for dates is the right call. Also improves potential future styling/localization.\n\nI'm a Reviewer so I can't apply these. Confirming my approval is contingent on these two fixes being applied. Once done, my consensus stands."
  }
}
